President Cyril Ramaphosa is set to unveil his much anticipated economic reconstruction and recovery plan. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa will outline South Africa’s economic reconstruction and recovery plan in Parliament on Thursday afternoon. Ramaphosa will address the National Assembly and the National Council of Provinces in a joint sitting. READ: Infrastructure investment could revive SA economy: Ramaphosa The recovery plan is the result of extensive deliberation between government and its social partners, including business and labour. 